summary:
I am a young professional, currently working as a teacher Bioinformatics at Hogeschool Leiden. I graduated the Master Molecular and Cellular Life Sciences with a profile in Bioinformatics. A fundamental research oriented master on the border of Chemistry and Biology. With a bachelor in Chemistry (also at Utrecht University) with a 3.64 GPA.

Besides my academic & professional achievements I enjoy a lot of sportive extracurricular activities. With a history in the Dutch national team of Korfball (male and female mixed sport) and a huge passion for snowboarding, wakeboarding and surfing, I developed a team oriented mindset and the ability to master difficult skills through persistence. I actively look for ways to translate the social and persistence skills in the academic and professional space.

Additional to these activities I have enjoyed multiple different part time jobs. Each of which taught a different skill, one of which was an unpaid board position as treasurer for more than a year. During this I got early and valuable experience running a small company.
